<p>As a Rogue, you start with 8 hit points plus your constitution modifier.
<input type="hidden" name="char_class" value="Rogue">
<input type="hidden" name="hit_point_max" value="8">
<p>You are proficient in Light Armor, Hand Crossbows, Longswords, Rapiers, and Shortswords</p>
<input type="hidden" name="prof[armor]" value="light armor">
<input type="hidden" name="prof[wep]" value="Hand Crossbows">
<input type="hidden" name="prof[wep]" value="Longswords">
<input type="hidden" name="prof[wep]" value="Rapiers">
<input type="hidden" name="prof[wep]" value="Shortswords">
<p>You are also proficient with Thieve's Tools.</p>
<input type="hidden" name="prof[tools]" value="martial weapons">

<p>You are proficient in saving throws of dexterity and intelligence.</p>
<input type="hidden" name="skill" value="dex_sav">
<input type="hidden" name="skill" value="int_sav">
<p>Choose four of the following skills</p>
<select 
  ng-options="skills as skills for skills in ctrl.selectedCharClass.possible_skills track by skills"
  ng-model="ctrl.charClassSkillsSelected"
  name="skill"
  multiple>
</select>
<p>You start with the following weapons</p>
<select
  ng-options="weapon as weapon for weapon in ctrl.selectedCharClass.wep_one track by weapon"
  ng-model="ctrl.charWep1Selected"
  name="equip[wep]"
></select>
<select
  ng-options="weapon2 as weapon2 for weapon2 in ctrl.selectedCharClass.wep_two track by weapon2"
  ng-model="ctrl.charWep2Selected"
  name="equip[wep]"
></select>

<p>You also start with the one of these packs</p>
<select
  ng-options="option as option for option in ctrl.selectedCharClass.opt_one track by option"
  ng-model="ctrl.charOpt1Selected"
  name="equip[gen]"
></select>

<p>You also start with Leather Armor, Two Daggers, and Thieve's tools</p>
<input type="hidden" name="equip[wep]" value="Two Daggers">
<input type="hidden" name="equip[armor]" value="Leather Armor">
<input type="hidden" name="equip[tools]" value="Thieve's Tools">

<p>You gain Expertise, choose 2 skills that you already have, or Thieve's tools, and whenever you make a check for that ability double your proficiency bonus.</p>
<input type="hidden" name="features" value="Expertise">

<select
  ng-options="skill as skill for skill in ctrl.selectedCharClass.possible_expertise track by skill"
  ng-model="ctrl.charExpSkill1Selected"
  name="features"
></select>
<select
  ng-options="skill as skill for skill in ctrl.selectedCharClass.possible_expertise track by skill"
  ng-model="ctrl.charExpSkill2Selected"
  name="features"
></select>

<p>You also gain Sneak Attack, lets you deal 1d6 damage once per turn to any creature you hit with an attack with which you have advantage on. You don't need advantage if another enemy of the target is within 5 feet of it. You must use a finesse or ranged weapon to use this.</p>
<input type="hidden" name="features", value="Sneak Attack">